modules.name: AWS.GuardDuty
modules.comments: Assess, monitor, manage, and remediate security issues across your AWS infrastructure, applications, and data.

declarations.comments: Accepts the invitation to be monitored by a master GuardDuty account.
declarations.title: acceptInvitation

declarations.comments: Archives Amazon GuardDuty findings specified by the list of finding IDs.
declarations.title: archiveFindings

declarations.comments: Creates a single Amazon GuardDuty detector. A detector is an object that represents the GuardDuty service. A detector must be created in order for GuardDuty to become operational.
declarations.title: createDetector

declarations.comments: Creates a new IPSet - a list of trusted IP addresses that have been whitelisted for secure communication with AWS infrastructure and applications.
declarations.title: createIPSet

declarations.comments: Creates member accounts of the current AWS account by specifying a list of AWS account IDs. The current AWS account can then invite these members to manage GuardDuty in their accounts.
declarations.title: createMembers

declarations.comments: Generates example findings of types specified by the list of finding types. If 'NULL' is specified for findingTypes, the API generates example findings of all supported finding types.
declarations.title: createSampleFindings

declarations.comments: Create a new ThreatIntelSet. ThreatIntelSets consist of known malicious IP addresses. GuardDuty generates findings based on ThreatIntelSets.
declarations.title: createThreatIntelSet

declarations.comments: Declines invitations sent to the current member account by AWS account specified by their account IDs.
declarations.title: declineInvitations

declarations.comments: Deletes a Amazon GuardDuty detector specified by the detector ID.
declarations.title: deleteDetector

declarations.comments: Deletes the IPSet specified by the IPSet ID.
declarations.title: deleteIPSet

declarations.comments: Deletes invitations sent to the current member account by AWS accounts specified by their account IDs.
declarations.title: deleteInvitations

declarations.comments: Deletes GuardDuty member accounts (to the current GuardDuty master account) specified by the account IDs.
declarations.title: deleteMembers

declarations.comments: Deletes ThreatIntelSet specified by the ThreatIntelSet ID.
declarations.title: deleteThreatIntelSet

declarations.comments: Disassociates the current GuardDuty member account from its master account.
declarations.title: disassociateFromMasterAccount

declarations.comments: Disassociates GuardDuty member accounts (to the current GuardDuty master account) specified by the account IDs.
declarations.title: disassociateMembers

declarations.comments: Retrieves an Amazon GuardDuty detector specified by the detectorId.
declarations.title: getDetector

declarations.comments: Describes Amazon GuardDuty findings specified by finding IDs.
declarations.title: getFindings

declarations.comments: Lists Amazon GuardDuty findings' statistics for the specified detector ID.
declarations.title: getFindingsStatistics

declarations.comments: Retrieves the IPSet specified by the IPSet ID.
declarations.title: getIPSet

declarations.comments: Returns the count of all GuardDuty membership invitations that were sent to the current member account except the currently accepted invitation.
declarations.title: getInvitationsCount

declarations.comments: Provides the details for the GuardDuty master account to the current GuardDuty member account.
declarations.title: getMasterAccount

declarations.comments: Retrieves GuardDuty member accounts (to the current GuardDuty master account) specified by the account IDs.
declarations.title: getMembers

declarations.comments: Retrieves the ThreatIntelSet that is specified by the ThreatIntelSet ID.
declarations.title: getThreatIntelSet

declarations.comments: Invites other AWS accounts (created as members of the current AWS account by CreateMembers) to enable GuardDuty and allow the current AWS account to view and manage these accounts' GuardDuty findings on their behalf as the master account.
declarations.title: inviteMembers

declarations.comments: Lists detectorIds of all the existing Amazon GuardDuty detector resources.
declarations.title: listDetectors

declarations.comments: Lists Amazon GuardDuty findings for the specified detector ID.
declarations.title: listFindings

declarations.comments: Lists the IPSets of the GuardDuty service specified by the detector ID.
declarations.title: listIPSets

declarations.comments: Lists all GuardDuty membership invitations that were sent to the current AWS account.
declarations.title: listInvitations

declarations.comments: Lists details about all member accounts for the current GuardDuty master account.
declarations.title: listMembers

declarations.comments: Lists the ThreatIntelSets of the GuardDuty service specified by the detector ID.
declarations.title: listThreatIntelSets

declarations.comments: Re-enables GuardDuty to monitor findings of the member accounts specified by the account IDs. A master GuardDuty account can run this command after disabling GuardDuty from monitoring these members' findings by running StopMonitoringMembers.
declarations.title: startMonitoringMembers

declarations.comments: Disables GuardDuty from monitoring findings of the member accounts specified by the account IDs. After running this command, a master GuardDuty account can run StartMonitoringMembers to re-enable GuardDuty to monitor these members' findings.
declarations.title: stopMonitoringMembers

declarations.comments: Unarchives Amazon GuardDuty findings specified by the list of finding IDs.
declarations.title: unarchiveFindings

declarations.comments: Updates an Amazon GuardDuty detector specified by the detectorId.
declarations.title: updateDetector

declarations.comments: Marks specified Amazon GuardDuty findings as useful or not useful.
declarations.title: updateFindingsFeedback

declarations.comments: Updates the IPSet specified by the IPSet ID.
declarations.title: updateIPSet

declarations.comments: Updates the ThreatIntelSet specified by ThreatIntelSet ID.
declarations.title: updateThreatIntelSet
